# Work tracking

Source of truth: `work/TW-NNN-*.md` files. Read `work/README.md` before claiming work.

## Before coding

1. `pnpm run work list --status active` — continue an active task if one exists.
2. Else `pnpm run work next [--area A] [--phase N]` then `pnpm run work claim TW-NNN`.
3. Branch `feat/TW-NNN-slug`. Read the full task file (Context, Scope, Acceptance).

## While working

- Tick acceptance checklist items in the task body as criteria pass.
- Append decisions to `## Log` with ISO dates.
- End every commit message with `Refs TW-NNN`.
- Open a **draft PR** on the first push (`git push -u origin HEAD` then `gh pr create --draft`) and update it on every push. Keep `status: active` until implementation is complete.

## Closing

1. When implementation is complete: publish the PR (`gh pr ready`), set `status: review`, fill `pr`, ensure `Closes TW-NNN` is in the PR body.
2. Wait for GitHub PR review and CI; fix findings until both are clean.
3. On merge: set `status: done`, `completed`, keep `pr`; run `pnpm run work index`.
4. Squash commit message must include `Closes TW-NNN` (derivation gate).

## After frontmatter edits

Run `pnpm run work index`. Never hand-edit `work/INDEX.md`.

## Before push

Run `pnpm check` and `pnpm run work check`.
